  "intro": {
    "headline": "Climate Snapshot: A Year in Lombardia",
    "tagline": "Where Alpine winters meet Mediterranean ambitions — four seasons with northern character.",
    "paragraphs": [
      "Lombardia lives between two worlds: the continental chill of the Po Valley and the moderating influence of its great lakes. The result is genuine four-season living — winter cold enough for snow, summers warm enough for lake swimming, and shoulder seasons that steal the show.",
      "The lakes create microclimates that surprise visitors. Como's western shore can be 5 degrees warmer than Milan on a winter day. The fog that blankets the plains rarely reaches the lakeside towns perched above. Choose your location carefully — climate varies dramatically across short distances.",
      "For those who crave seasonal change without extremes, Lombardia delivers. You'll need a winter coat, yes, but you'll also enjoy spring blossoms, summer evenings, and golden autumns that make every photograph look composed."
    ],
    "hoverQuote": "In Lombardia, the fog lifts and suddenly the Alps appear — that never gets old.",
